1
00:00:10,967 --> 00:00:11,400
<i> Hey!</i>

2
00:00:11,533 --> 00:00:12,600
<i> Who are you?</i>

3
00:00:12,733 --> 00:00:14,967
<i>- Come here! You're a maniac!
- Don't hurt him!</i>

4
00:00:15,100 --> 00:00:16,633
<i> Don't! Don't!</i>

5
00:00:16,767 --> 00:00:17,867
<i> Cherry, what are you doing?</i>

6
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:20,267
<i>We're saving you. Isn't he
taking advantage of you?</i>

7
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:21,567
<i> He's my boyfriend!</i>

8
00:00:21,700 --> 00:00:22,900
<i> He's your boyfriend?</i>

9
00:00:24,133 --> 00:00:26,433
<i> Where are the girls?</i>

10
00:00:26,567 --> 00:00:27,567
<i> Where did they go?</i>

11
00:00:27,700 --> 00:00:28,567
<i> They're...</i>

12
00:00:28,700 --> 00:00:30,633
<i>they're taking them
to Switzerland.</i>

13
00:00:30,767 --> 00:00:33,300
<i>Yes, Sir. We have to go
to Switzerland.</i>

14
00:00:33,433 --> 00:00:34,667
<i> You can't.</i>

15
00:00:34,833 --> 00:00:37,833
<i>Your remaining budget is just
enough to bring Selena back.</i>

16
00:00:39,400 --> 00:00:40,933
<i>- What's that?
- Where are you taking her?</i>

17
00:00:41,067 --> 00:00:42,167
<i>The captain has been kidnapped!</i>

18
00:00:42,300 --> 00:00:44,367
<i>- Councilor!
- Okay, get in, get in.</i>

19
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:45,367
<i> Hello, Major.</i>

20
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:46,867
<i>Sir, I can't believe
I'm saying this,</i>

21
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:50,033
<i>but I'm going to find Reign even
if it means ruining my career.</i>

22
00:00:50,167 --> 00:00:51,467
<i>Do you remember
the plate number?</i>

23
00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:54,033
<i> Yes, ANQ 1013.</i>

24
00:00:54,167 --> 00:00:54,567
<i> A red van!</i>

25
00:00:54,700 --> 00:00:55,933
<i> Let me out!</i>

26
00:00:56,067 --> 00:00:57,300
<i> Did I do something wrong?</i>

27
00:00:57,433 --> 00:00:57,767
<i> Grandmother?</i>

28
00:00:57,900 --> 00:00:58,767
<i> You animal!</i>

29
00:00:58,900 --> 00:01:00,267
<i>What are you doing
to my grandmother?</i>

30
00:01:00,400 --> 00:01:02,400
<i>I know you have Selena Madrigal
with you.</i>

31
00:01:02,533 --> 00:01:03,567
<i> Give her back to me,</i>

32
00:01:03,700 --> 00:01:05,867
<i>or I'll blow your grandmother's
head off.</i>

33
00:01:09,367 --> 00:01:12,533
For sure, Chief,
they got Enriquez's profile,

34
00:01:12,667 --> 00:01:14,567
so they also found out
about her grandmother.

35
00:01:14,700 --> 00:01:16,067
But the good news is,

36
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:18,267
it seems they don't know
anything about Reign

37
00:01:18,400 --> 00:01:20,067
because they haven't mentioned
anything yet.

38
00:01:20,200 --> 00:01:22,233
And, Chief, the bad news is,

39
00:01:22,367 --> 00:01:26,867
we can't send Selena back
to the syndicate, right?

40
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:27,500
Yes.

41
00:01:29,967 --> 00:01:31,833
I am very sorry, Enriquez,

42
00:01:31,967 --> 00:01:33,467
because your grandmother
got involved.

43
00:01:33,600 --> 00:01:37,067
Like what I said,
Selena is our priority.

44
00:01:37,200 --> 00:01:38,767
Sir, what's the update
on my grandmother?

45
00:01:38,900 --> 00:01:41,300
Don't worry, Enriquez. Trust me.

46
00:01:41,467 --> 00:01:45,633
We are still looking for the van
used by the kidnappers.

47
00:01:45,767 --> 00:01:47,167
If I were you, Enriquez,

48
00:01:47,300 --> 00:01:51,200
I would delay the exchange
until we find your grandmother.

49
00:01:51,333 --> 00:01:52,767
Sir, I'm going home.

50
00:01:52,900 --> 00:01:55,000
I will help find grandmother.

51
00:01:57,167 --> 00:01:58,767
What about your godsister?

52
00:02:41,100 --> 00:02:43,100
What, Enriquez? Have you found
any flights yet?

53
00:02:46,067 --> 00:02:50,000
Sir, the earliest flight
tomorrow is at 6:30 am.

54
00:02:50,167 --> 00:02:52,467
The travel time is 15 hours.

55
00:02:52,600 --> 00:02:55,433
That's a very long wait.

56
00:02:55,567 --> 00:02:57,100
What if, by the time I get back
to the Philippines,

57
00:02:57,233 --> 00:02:58,933
something bad has already
happened to grandmother?

58
00:03:04,533 --> 00:03:06,900
I don't know if this will help,
Enriquez...

59
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,933
but I have an OFW friend.

60
00:03:11,100 --> 00:03:12,900
He also has an emergency
in the Philippines.

61
00:03:14,300 --> 00:03:15,700
He didn't get home
right away either.

62
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:18,467
The truth is...

63
00:03:19,433 --> 00:03:23,133
many of our countrymen are going
through the same thing.

64
00:03:26,700 --> 00:03:28,567
So don't lose hope.

65
00:03:28,700 --> 00:03:30,833
Chief and the others will save
your grandmother.

66
00:03:40,033 --> 00:03:41,433
This is all my fault, Sir.

67
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:44,367
That's why my grandmother
got involved too.

68
00:03:47,433 --> 00:03:48,567
Enriquez...

69
00:03:49,933 --> 00:03:52,233
don't make it a habit to assume

70
00:03:52,367 --> 00:03:54,167
that whenever something
bad happens,

71
00:03:54,333 --> 00:03:55,733
it's your fault right away.

72
00:03:57,833 --> 00:03:59,367
This is what you should do.

73
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:01,567
The next time you talk
to the syndicate...

74
00:04:03,567 --> 00:04:05,867
just make excuses.

75
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:08,200
Tell them...

76
00:04:08,333 --> 00:04:09,733
Selena escaped.

77
00:04:12,100 --> 00:04:13,767
Tell them everything,
do everything,

78
00:04:13,900 --> 00:04:18,033
so they will agree to delay
the exchange.

79
00:04:18,167 --> 00:04:20,633
Wouldn't Godmother Dina
be mad at me

80
00:04:20,767 --> 00:04:23,433
if I prioritize
my grandmother first?

81
00:04:27,767 --> 00:04:29,967
You already went to Dubai.

82
00:04:30,100 --> 00:04:32,867
Now, we're here in Milan
to save your godsister.

83
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,733
You did everything you can,
Enriquez.

84
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:41,933
I'm sure your godmother
appreciates that.

85
00:04:42,067 --> 00:04:43,033
And what's with you?

86
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:46,533
We're going to save
your godsister.

87
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:49,167
Just don't lose hope.

88
00:04:54,967 --> 00:04:55,733
Okay, Sir.

89
00:04:57,033 --> 00:04:58,267
I'll call Markus.

90
00:05:10,500 --> 00:05:12,233
Sergeant Enriquez,

91
00:05:12,367 --> 00:05:14,933
we were supposed to meet
at eight o'clock.

92
00:05:15,067 --> 00:05:17,767
You must be too excited
to save your grandmother.

93
00:05:17,900 --> 00:05:19,900
Markus, we have a problem.

94
00:05:20,033 --> 00:05:21,733
Selena is missing.

95
00:05:21,867 --> 00:05:24,067
Stop messing around,
Sergeant Enriquez.

96
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:25,133
What do you mean she's missing?

97
00:05:26,767 --> 00:05:28,167
I'm not messing with you.

98
00:05:29,767 --> 00:05:31,667
She overheard what we were
talking about earlier,

99
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:32,700
so she escaped.

100
00:05:32,833 --> 00:05:34,267
That's not my problem anymore!

101
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:39,667
Fine.

102
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:41,000
One hour...

103
00:05:42,133 --> 00:05:44,500
or else your grandmother
will be dead.

104
00:05:44,633 --> 00:05:46,133
One hour?

105
00:05:46,267 --> 00:05:47,767
Markus, that's not possible!

106
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:51,567
If you really love
your grandmother...

107
00:05:51,700 --> 00:05:52,500
Markus!

108
00:05:53,700 --> 00:05:54,733
Markus!

109
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:07,433
Enriquez, where are you going?

110
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:10,267
I will take Selena to them!

111
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:12,767
Otherwise, they'll kill
my grandmother!

112
00:06:12,900 --> 00:06:16,733
You heard it earlier, right?
So don't stop me!

113
00:06:18,300 --> 00:06:20,200
Well then, take me to them.

114
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:26,433
You won't let anything bad
happen to me, right?

115
00:06:39,367 --> 00:06:43,100
Oh my, we'll be in trouble with
Chief when this gets to him.

116
00:06:44,433 --> 00:06:48,167
That's why we have to do our
best so it doesn't get to him.

117
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:52,167
Enriquez really has
a strong hold on you.

118
00:06:53,633 --> 00:06:55,433
Hey, you're crazy.

119
00:06:58,200 --> 00:06:59,900
The exchange is coming up.

120
00:07:01,433 --> 00:07:03,233
Are you ready, Enriquez?

121
00:07:03,367 --> 00:07:04,233
Yes, Sir.

122
00:07:13,467 --> 00:07:14,267
Hello?

123
00:07:14,433 --> 00:07:15,467
What?

124
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:17,167
Do you have Selena with you?

125
00:07:17,300 --> 00:07:18,500
She's with me.

126
00:07:18,633 --> 00:07:20,800
I want to hear her voice.

127
00:07:25,333 --> 00:07:26,667
Let me go.

128
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:27,700
Fools!

129
00:07:27,833 --> 00:07:29,467
I thought you were good cops.

130
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:31,800
Let me go! Let me go!

131
00:07:31,933 --> 00:07:34,367
There, you can do it.

132
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:37,900
You heard Selena already.

133
00:07:38,033 --> 00:07:40,267
Let my grandmother go.

134
00:07:40,400 --> 00:07:43,100
Are you kidding me,
Sergeant Enriquez?

135
00:07:43,233 --> 00:07:46,100
We're talking about
an exchange deal.

136
00:07:46,233 --> 00:07:50,400
Selena, in exchange
for your grandmother.

137
00:07:50,567 --> 00:07:53,600
How can I be sure
that you won't betray me?

138
00:07:53,733 --> 00:07:55,600
Why? Do you have a choice?

139
00:07:55,733 --> 00:07:59,367
Take Selena to the place
we talked about.

140
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:01,000
I'm on my way.

141
00:08:05,900 --> 00:08:08,000
Any update on my grandmother,
Sir?

142
00:08:08,133 --> 00:08:10,433
It's still negative, Enriquez.

143
00:08:10,567 --> 00:08:14,800
So we don't have a choice now
but to follow them.

144
00:08:16,533 --> 00:08:18,367
Don't worry, Selena.

145
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:20,300
Garcia and I will be keeping
an eye on you.

146
00:08:23,133 --> 00:08:23,900
We'll stay there.

147
00:08:24,033 --> 00:08:24,800
Let's go.

148
00:08:24,933 --> 00:08:25,867
Okay.

149
00:09:14,700 --> 00:09:15,933
What will happen now?

150
00:09:16,067 --> 00:09:17,400
We've been going around
and around for a while now.

151
00:09:17,533 --> 00:09:19,700
Until now, we haven't seen
the red van.

152
00:09:19,833 --> 00:09:21,633
Oh my, I hope there's a miracle.

153
00:09:21,767 --> 00:09:23,733
I hope we can save
Grandmother Isang.

154
00:09:23,867 --> 00:09:24,633
Thank you.

155
00:09:25,733 --> 00:09:26,433
They've seen the van.

156
00:09:26,567 --> 00:09:27,500
Oh my, thank you.

157
00:09:27,667 --> 00:09:29,433
My God. Thank you, Lord.

158
00:09:29,567 --> 00:09:30,667
They'll send me the location.

159
00:09:30,800 --> 00:09:31,600
- Let's go.
- Let's go, go, go.

160
00:09:31,733 --> 00:09:33,400
- Quick, quick. Let's go.
- Let's go.

161
00:10:26,100 --> 00:10:27,600
Are you sure that's the van?

162
00:10:27,733 --> 00:10:28,867
That's it, that's it.

163
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:29,867
The red van. Yes, that's it.

164
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:31,100
The red van.

165
00:10:31,233 --> 00:10:35,033
- Okay, okay. Wait, wait.
- Let's go in! Let's go in!

166
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:36,000
Lee, Bal!

167
00:10:37,933 --> 00:10:41,033
Faye, call Major Flores.
Send them our location.

168
00:10:41,933 --> 00:10:44,200
Glen, what are you going to do?

169
00:10:47,833 --> 00:10:49,067
- Glen, oh my gosh...
- Faye...

170
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:50,067
stay here.

171
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:51,300
Councilor...

172
00:10:51,433 --> 00:10:53,300
You take care of my sister.

173
00:10:53,433 --> 00:10:54,333
Stay in the car.

174
00:10:54,467 --> 00:10:55,067
Glen!

175
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:56,133
Faye, Faye, Faye!

176
00:10:57,967 --> 00:10:58,767
Glen!

177
00:10:58,900 --> 00:11:00,367
Faye, later!
Stay in the car first.

178
00:11:15,733 --> 00:11:18,133
- Hey, hide.
- Mar, here! Get down!

179
00:11:20,333 --> 00:11:21,100
Lee, Bal.

180
00:11:21,233 --> 00:11:21,867
Let's split up.

181
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:23,067
Yes, okay.

182
00:11:23,200 --> 00:11:25,533
- Let's find Captain Isang.
- Okay, okay. Let's go.

183
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:27,633
- Bro.
- Hey!

184
00:11:36,900 --> 00:11:38,367
Where's Captain Isang?

185
00:11:38,500 --> 00:11:39,467
Where is she?

186
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:40,967
Hurry! Someone might be there.

187
00:11:44,133 --> 00:11:45,533
Let's go.

188
00:11:46,667 --> 00:11:47,700
What are you doing here?

189
00:11:50,900 --> 00:11:52,633
I'm a majorette.

190
00:11:52,767 --> 00:11:53,967
How about you?

191
00:11:54,100 --> 00:11:55,367
I'm an electric fan.

192
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:56,267
How about you?

193
00:11:57,900 --> 00:11:59,133
I'm rowing.

194
00:11:59,267 --> 00:12:00,400
How about you?

195
00:12:04,900 --> 00:12:05,667
I'm rowing.

196
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:07,400
Row over there!

197
00:12:07,533 --> 00:12:08,333
Stupid!

198
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:12,067
Hey!

199
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:19,267
Boss!

200
00:12:19,400 --> 00:12:20,500
Just kidding, Boss!

201
00:12:21,867 --> 00:12:23,467
Boss, I'm just kidding!

202
00:12:37,967 --> 00:12:39,067
Amazing!

203
00:12:40,833 --> 00:12:41,567
Let's go.

204
00:12:52,833 --> 00:12:53,833
Hey!

205
00:12:53,967 --> 00:12:54,633
Oh my gosh!

206
00:12:54,767 --> 00:12:55,533
- That was a gunshot!
- Faye!

207
00:12:55,667 --> 00:12:56,900
Yes, Faye!
Get inside the car, Faye!

208
00:12:57,033 --> 00:12:59,333
- Where's Glen? Glen!
- Faye!

209
00:13:08,400 --> 00:13:11,367
Let me out of here!

210
00:13:11,500 --> 00:13:13,500
Help! Help!

211
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:17,133
What? We've got two down,
haven't we?

212
00:13:17,267 --> 00:13:18,933
- Yes, man.
- How many more?

213
00:13:19,067 --> 00:13:20,767
What? Have you seen
Captain Isang?

214
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:22,367
- No.
- We haven't seen her yet.

215
00:13:22,533 --> 00:13:24,733
- Hey! Hands up!
- Mister! Mister!

216
00:13:24,867 --> 00:13:27,100
Put all your things down!

217
00:13:27,233 --> 00:13:28,267
- Put it down!
- Sorry.

218
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:29,600
- Put it down!
- Yes, okay.

219
00:13:29,733 --> 00:13:32,900
Have mercy!

220
00:13:33,033 --> 00:13:33,800
Abdul!

221
00:13:33,933 --> 00:13:34,967
Pray now!

222
00:13:35,100 --> 00:13:37,433
- No, no!
- You're going to die now!

223
00:13:59,367 --> 00:14:00,033
Boss?

224
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:03,200
Where did you hide
the old woman?

225
00:14:03,333 --> 00:14:04,700
In the greenhouse.

226
00:14:06,033 --> 00:14:07,300
Okay, you'd better leave.

227
00:14:07,433 --> 00:14:08,433
Copy, Boss.

228
00:14:08,567 --> 00:14:09,267
Let's go.

229
00:14:24,933 --> 00:14:26,133
All clear, Sir.

230
00:14:29,367 --> 00:14:31,500
Councilor, are you okay?

231
00:14:31,633 --> 00:14:33,000
Yes, I'm okay.

232
00:14:34,067 --> 00:14:36,233
The important thing is
to find Captain Isang.

233
00:14:37,933 --> 00:14:39,067
Let's go.

234
00:15:08,333 --> 00:15:09,033
Hands up!

235
00:15:09,167 --> 00:15:10,600
- Hands up!
- We are the police!

236
00:15:10,733 --> 00:15:14,100
Hands up!

237
00:15:14,667 --> 00:15:15,900
Put down your guns!

238
00:15:16,033 --> 00:15:17,600
- Get down. Get down!
- We're safe.

239
00:15:17,733 --> 00:15:19,433
Fools!

240
00:15:19,567 --> 00:15:20,733
You said it's our end?

241
00:15:22,067 --> 00:15:23,767
You said it's our end?

242
00:15:23,900 --> 00:15:25,400
You're shameless!

243
00:15:25,533 --> 00:15:27,233
Where's your bravery now?

244
00:15:27,367 --> 00:15:29,367
Take those guys out!

245
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:30,300
Get up!

246
00:15:30,433 --> 00:15:31,200
Here.

247
00:15:32,867 --> 00:15:34,000
Here. Get down there, get down.

248
00:15:34,133 --> 00:15:35,300
Sir! Sir!

249
00:15:35,467 --> 00:15:37,633
- Let's find Captain Isang.
- We still haven't found her.

250
00:15:37,767 --> 00:15:39,300
We still haven't found her yet,
Sir.

251
00:15:39,433 --> 00:15:40,933
What a pity, Sir.
Let's find her, Sir.

252
00:15:41,067 --> 00:15:42,100
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

253
00:15:43,633 --> 00:15:46,667
- Glen? Glen!
- Hey, wait. Don't shout, Faye!

254
00:15:46,800 --> 00:15:48,367
- Hey! Where are you going?
- Glen!

255
00:15:48,500 --> 00:15:49,433
Stay here.

256
00:15:49,567 --> 00:15:51,100
Here, hurry up!

257
00:15:51,233 --> 00:15:51,900
Wait!

258
00:15:53,100 --> 00:15:53,933
You're so slow.

259
00:16:05,767 --> 00:16:08,500
- Faye, let's go. Faye!
- Glen?

260
00:16:08,667 --> 00:16:11,267
- Faye, let's go!
- Glen! I have to save Glen!

261
00:16:11,400 --> 00:16:16,767
Glen! Glen!

262
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:23,333
Let me go!

263
00:16:26,033 --> 00:16:26,667
Go.

264
00:16:29,300 --> 00:16:31,133
Captain!

265
00:16:37,333 --> 00:16:39,100
Thank you!

266
00:16:39,233 --> 00:16:39,967
Mar!

267
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:43,300
Captain, I'm here.

268
00:16:46,267 --> 00:16:50,000
- Hurry, hurry.
- Captain!

269
00:16:50,133 --> 00:16:52,400
Thank you. You helped me,
thank you!

270
00:16:52,533 --> 00:16:54,267
- We saved you!
- Thank you.

271
00:16:54,400 --> 00:16:56,433
We thought we wouldn't see
you again, Captain.

272
00:16:56,567 --> 00:16:57,567
Sir, let's go.

273
00:16:57,700 --> 00:16:58,967
Let's move out.

274
00:16:59,100 --> 00:17:00,100
Let's go.

275
00:17:01,433 --> 00:17:02,700
Roman!

276
00:17:02,833 --> 00:17:05,133
Stay away from that old woman
for now.

277
00:17:05,267 --> 00:17:08,133
You might get wounded
if I blow her head off.

278
00:17:09,567 --> 00:17:11,167
Markus, there's a problem.

279
00:17:13,833 --> 00:17:14,867
There's a little glitch.

280
00:17:15,033 --> 00:17:16,100
What glitch?

281
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:19,867
Someone interfered.

282
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:21,967
Enriquez's grandmother managed
to escape.

283
00:17:31,267 --> 00:17:32,633
Sorry, Selena.

284
00:17:34,333 --> 00:17:36,233
You got caught up in our plan.

285
00:17:39,267 --> 00:17:41,333
You survived the syndicate,

286
00:17:41,467 --> 00:17:44,067
but here we are,
putting your life in danger.

287
00:17:46,033 --> 00:17:49,400
Don't worry too much about me,
Miss Bobby.

288
00:17:49,567 --> 00:17:50,567
You know...

289
00:17:51,833 --> 00:17:55,400
I really trust you
and Sir Tonyo.

290
00:17:55,533 --> 00:17:58,400
You've saved me so many times.

291
00:17:58,533 --> 00:18:02,767
Up until here in Milan,
you still helped me.

292
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:06,267
Now, let me do the same.

293
00:18:06,400 --> 00:18:08,500
It's my turn.

294
00:18:08,633 --> 00:18:09,600
Thank you.

295
00:18:17,033 --> 00:18:17,967
Hello, Sir!

296
00:18:23,700 --> 00:18:24,467
Yes, Sir!

297
00:18:26,533 --> 00:18:27,867
Why did his eyes grow big?

298
00:18:30,967 --> 00:18:32,067
Enriquez!

299
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:33,200
Your grandmother...

300
00:18:36,167 --> 00:18:38,000
Your grandmother...

301
00:18:38,133 --> 00:18:39,200
is safe already.

302
00:18:47,733 --> 00:18:48,767
Thank you, Sir.

303
00:18:52,767 --> 00:18:54,667
Thank you, Sir.

304
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:56,867
God is truly merciful.

305
00:18:57,033 --> 00:18:59,100
Ma'am Bobby, your grandmother
is safe already.

306
00:19:07,500 --> 00:19:10,067
You're really making me angry,
Sergeant Enriquez!

307
00:19:10,200 --> 00:19:11,667
You outsmarted me
with your grandmother!

308
00:19:11,800 --> 00:19:13,067
You're going to regret this!

309
00:19:19,700 --> 00:19:22,200
Come on, let's get out of here.

310
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:28,333
I'll take care of this.

311
00:19:28,500 --> 00:19:30,333
Get out of here.

312
00:19:30,467 --> 00:19:32,333
Go ahead!

313
00:19:32,467 --> 00:19:33,133
Let's go.

314
00:19:56,700 --> 00:19:58,100
What do you have to say
about the hostage taking?

315
00:19:58,233 --> 00:19:59,500
- Sir...
- Robles...

316
00:19:59,633 --> 00:20:02,233
- There's Captain Isang.
- Captain?

317
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:03,233
Chief...

318
00:20:03,367 --> 00:20:04,233
Grandmother Isang!

319
00:20:04,367 --> 00:20:06,300
- Thank you, thank you.
- Are you okay?

320
00:20:06,433 --> 00:20:07,233
Yes.

321
00:20:09,100 --> 00:20:11,067
Thank you. Thank you so much
to our police force.

322
00:20:11,200 --> 00:20:15,233
Do you know the person
behind the kidnapping?

323
00:20:15,367 --> 00:20:18,967
Councilor, thank you,
thank you so much.

324
00:20:19,100 --> 00:20:21,767
Captain, the important thing
is that you are safe.

325
00:20:23,567 --> 00:20:25,567
- Thank you.
- De Jesus, Torres...

326
00:20:25,700 --> 00:20:26,800
get them out of here.

327
00:20:38,733 --> 00:20:39,467
Enriquez...

328
00:20:40,867 --> 00:20:42,367
someone wants to talk to you.

329
00:20:43,800 --> 00:20:44,567
Grandmother Isang...

330
00:20:45,767 --> 00:20:46,700
this is Bobby.

331
00:20:49,867 --> 00:20:50,600
Grandchild.

332
00:20:50,733 --> 00:20:51,900
Grandmother!

333
00:20:52,033 --> 00:20:53,867
Grandmother, how are you?

334
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:55,167
Grandchild...

335
00:20:55,300 --> 00:20:56,633
Don't worry.

336
00:20:57,800 --> 00:20:59,700
I'm okay, I'm okay.

337
00:20:59,833 --> 00:21:03,000
The police officers saved me.

338
00:21:03,133 --> 00:21:04,833
Grandmother, I'm sorry.

339
00:21:04,967 --> 00:21:08,067
Sorry, you got caught up
in our mission, Grandmother.

340
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:10,333
I'm so sorry.

341
00:21:10,500 --> 00:21:13,633
I thought my life was in danger.

342
00:21:13,767 --> 00:21:14,900
I thought I was going to die

343
00:21:15,033 --> 00:21:16,567
and we'll never see
each other again.

344
00:21:16,700 --> 00:21:17,933
I'm going home now.

345
00:21:19,433 --> 00:21:20,800
Wait for me, okay?

346
00:21:20,933 --> 00:21:21,433
What?

347
00:21:21,567 --> 00:21:23,233
You're going home?

348
00:21:23,367 --> 00:21:24,833
What about Reign?

349
00:21:24,967 --> 00:21:28,033
Save her! Look for her!

350
00:21:28,167 --> 00:21:31,833
Don't go home without her!

351
00:21:31,967 --> 00:21:33,700
<i>Don't worry about me,
Grandchild.</i>

352
00:21:33,833 --> 00:21:36,233
I'm okay.

353
00:21:36,367 --> 00:21:37,633
The kid...

354
00:21:37,767 --> 00:21:39,833
Save the kid.

355
00:21:39,967 --> 00:21:40,867
Okay, Grandmother.

356
00:21:42,800 --> 00:21:44,400
I'll save Reign.

357
00:21:44,533 --> 00:21:46,533
Be careful, Grandchild.

358
00:21:46,667 --> 00:21:48,367
Be careful.

359
00:22:03,667 --> 00:22:06,267
Bok, I'll search
for our flight home.

360
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:09,533
Most likely, we'll be able
to fly out tomorrow.

361
00:22:11,967 --> 00:22:13,333
Enriquez, what's your plan?

362
00:22:15,367 --> 00:22:17,233
I'll stay behind, Sir.

363
00:22:17,367 --> 00:22:19,267
I'll find Reign in Switzerland.

364
00:22:19,400 --> 00:22:20,933
You'll do it alone, Ma'am Bobby?

365
00:22:21,067 --> 00:22:24,600
You know, you're really my idol.

366
00:22:24,733 --> 00:22:28,400
If I could just come with you,
I would.

367
00:22:28,533 --> 00:22:32,967
Oh my, Selena, I don't want to
put your life in danger anymore.

368
00:22:33,100 --> 00:22:34,200
It's clear to me

369
00:22:34,333 --> 00:22:37,500
that the priority of this
mission is to get you home.

370
00:22:41,067 --> 00:22:42,033
I'll go ahead, Sir.

371
00:22:42,167 --> 00:22:43,600
I'm going to pack.

372
00:22:57,500 --> 00:23:01,100
Are you sure about that plan
of yours, Enriquez?

373
00:23:01,233 --> 00:23:05,233
As for me, I'm willing to leave
my credit card with you

374
00:23:05,367 --> 00:23:09,733
because my credit limit is high.

375
00:23:09,867 --> 00:23:12,733
But what's your plan?

376
00:23:12,867 --> 00:23:14,633
Are you going to attack
the enemies,

377
00:23:14,767 --> 00:23:16,200
the syndicate, all by yourself?

378
00:23:19,067 --> 00:23:21,700
I need to save my godsister,
Sir.

379
00:23:23,067 --> 00:23:25,567
I don't want to put Selena's
life in danger.

380
00:23:28,300 --> 00:23:32,667
With that decision of yours,
are you ready to be suspended?

381
00:23:39,600 --> 00:23:40,900
I'm sorry, Enriquez.

382
00:23:42,133 --> 00:23:44,267
We have to go back
to the Philippines.

383
00:23:46,367 --> 00:23:51,533
Just call me if you need
anything, okay?

384
00:23:53,067 --> 00:23:54,867
Yes, Sir, take care.

385
00:23:56,100 --> 00:23:57,267
Okay, Enriquez.

386
00:23:57,400 --> 00:23:58,200
Okay, Sir!

387
00:24:16,667 --> 00:24:17,633
Enriquez!

388
00:24:24,600 --> 00:24:25,367
Sir?

389
00:24:29,333 --> 00:24:30,400
Well...

390
00:24:31,800 --> 00:24:33,600
I've already been
suspended before...

391
00:24:35,633 --> 00:24:37,833
so it's probably okay
if it happens again.

392
00:24:43,800 --> 00:24:45,400
Thank you, Sir.

393
00:24:45,533 --> 00:24:46,467
Thank you.

394
00:24:48,200 --> 00:24:48,867
How about you, Sir?

395
00:24:50,833 --> 00:24:51,433
What...

396
00:24:52,967 --> 00:24:55,633
I haven't been suspended yet,
but...

397
00:24:55,767 --> 00:24:57,900
but what will you do without me?

398
00:24:58,033 --> 00:25:00,067
I'm the best among
the three of us.

399
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:03,733
Okay, fine.
I'll come with you too.

400
00:25:03,900 --> 00:25:04,900
Thank you, Sir.

401
00:25:06,667 --> 00:25:09,433
Why do I only get a high five,
while he gets a hug?

402
00:25:09,567 --> 00:25:10,867
That's okay, Bok.

403
00:25:12,167 --> 00:25:13,667
Enriquez,

404
00:25:13,800 --> 00:25:14,933
we'll come with you.

405
00:25:17,000 --> 00:25:18,367
We'll save Reign.

406
00:25:19,600 --> 00:25:20,833
Thank you, Sir!

407
00:25:20,967 --> 00:25:21,867
Thank you!

408
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:23,367
Oh my...

409
00:25:23,600 --> 00:25:26,500
I knew it, you were just shy
to ask Bok earlier.

410
00:25:26,633 --> 00:25:28,300
Move on, I already have Cecilia.

411
00:25:43,633 --> 00:25:45,700
Sir, come on, let's go inside.

412
00:25:45,833 --> 00:25:46,667
Wait a minute, Enriquez.

413
00:25:46,800 --> 00:25:48,233
We're not familiar
with the inside yet.

414
00:25:48,367 --> 00:25:50,700
If we miss this, we might
not be able to save Reign.

415
00:25:50,833 --> 00:25:52,433
Look, there are guards.

416
00:25:52,567 --> 00:25:54,200
If only Selena was here.

417
00:25:54,333 --> 00:25:56,900
We could use her
as a distraction.

418
00:25:59,467 --> 00:26:01,533
Looks like the house upstairs
is just their front.

419
00:26:01,667 --> 00:26:03,600
Looks like this is their
center of operations.

420
00:26:03,733 --> 00:26:05,600
Sir, they might
auction Reign here.

421
00:26:05,733 --> 00:26:06,700
Enriquez...

422
00:26:07,667 --> 00:26:08,600
be careful.

423
00:26:08,767 --> 00:26:09,367
Yes, Sir.

424
00:26:09,500 --> 00:26:11,133
Everybody, put your hands up!
